To be serious, advice for all our American cousins, when in Europe,
forget all this retail, booking price, Martha Stewart, and what one would
&quot;expect&quot; nonsense, if you adopt this kinda attitude you'll get well and
truly ripped.

Look at the stuff, if you are REALLY interested, ask the dealer &quot;what he
needs&quot; for the item then take it from there, if it's still too much after
the haggling, then bid the dealer YOUR price, start the haggling again
and with a bit of luck and good humour you'll both settle somewhere in
the middle. Splitting the difference is what we call it over here. At the
end of the day, if you both can't agree on the price then no hard
feelings, you'll do a deal maybe the next time around. Don't burn your
bridges or cut your nose off to spite your face.

Best of luck. ;&gt;)

btw Jon .. have you ever tossed a coin to close the deal. Ya know, the
