Except for the rolling dice or flipping a coin to decide a price, things
are pretty much the same over here. It's against the law in Texas to
offer a lower price for cash than you offer for a credit card (don't ask
me why, it's never made any sense to me either) but in practice you
always get a slightly better deal for cash.

Most dealers build in a little negotiating room, and how low they're
willing to go bears a direct realtionship to how long the piece has been
gathering dust, and an inverse relationship to the amount they've
already sold that month. You also get a better deal right before the
rent is due on a slow month.

Richard Ward

